      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GALLOPING JESSIE (1) missed the frame latest when seventh at Traralgon (24.77) but was a winner four back in the best time of the program. Has ability and looks hard to stop. FANCY FAYE (5) was big odds last time but gave a huge sight after a fast early split, grabbed late but holding on to a placing when a 1.3 lengths second (22.90) over 400m at Geelong. Some good form is emerging from her last run. Expected to be in this for a long way. RUMOUR I'M BROKE (2) is mixing form lately, finishing out of the placings last time at Healesville but was a T3 Grade 6 winner two back at Healesville. Can improve sharply here. ROADS END (6) will make his presence felt following a brief layoff.",
